Package: pbph
Title: Peters-Belson with Prognostic Heterogeneity
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Josh", "Errickson", email = "josh@errickson.net", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Produces proper estimates in the Peters-Belson with Prognostic Heterogeneity
    method; to address whether there is an interaction between predicted outcome and
    treatment. This generally arise when testing hypotheses of the form "Do those most at
    risk (predicted to have a low outcome in the absence of treatment) gain more effect
    from the treatment?"
Depends: R (>= 3.1)
License: GPL-3
LazyData: true
Imports:
    sandwich,
    methods,
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat,
    roxygen2,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    covr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
